06/05/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Former Prime Minister Aleksander Meksi announced on Tuesday (May 5th) his decision to return to active politics and to run in the June parliamentary elections as a candidate of the right-wing Movement for National Development.
Meksi was the first post-communist prime minister in Albania, serving between 1992 and 1997.
Once the leader of the ruling Democratic Party, Meksi will now run against it.
(Shekulli, VoA, Top Channel, News 24 - 05/05/09)
